cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper presents a general-purpose method for weakly supervised learning that can be applied to any weak supervision regime or model. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and computer vision, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a loss function to specify weak supervision regimes, which could also relate to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
